<br>
I have been reading and gathering information on the status of Califario. I've tried to figure out how a non citizen simply walked off with someone elses colony and gave it to Shireroth. I wasn't able to contact anyone from Shireroth to get their opinion so instead I used the threads in their board. In which Shireroth seem to instead of participating in common sense said &quot;It's ours.&quot; in brief. To clarify and maybe enlighten some whom haven't explored this situation. <br>
<br>
Califario is a colony, part of the Republic of Amerada. Earl Washburn, Chris Sullivan (Also known as TXsocialist) tried to perform a communist revolution. However This so called Revolution was put in it's place by the administration and life went on. Sometime before the revolution was destroyed it seems the prior governor of the colony Califario emigrated from The Republic of Amerada. He gives up his status as governor by doing this you see. As Californio is not a protectorate, or an independant nation of any kind, it is simply a colony. Matt informed Nicholas Bridgewater that he'd give him the password for the board, and web-page. <br>
<br>
Well Matt whom I don't know so can't comment on his character decided instead to give away a colony that wasn't his to give away. Shireroth gladly accepted another territory all of this taking place without informing The Republic of Amerada. Now both sides says they have Californio. So what's the opinion in all this? If someone whom wasn't my citizen of my nation, said &quot;Hmm I like this colony.&quot; Spends a term as governor then emigrates, then during a revolution goes &quot;Well they look busy... &quot; So goes and gives the colony to his friends. <br>
<br>
All the while Shireroth is pretending to hold a Territory the Republic of Amerada has appointed Angus McSoto as the current governier. Bridgewater being the diplomat he is has been cordial with Shireroth simply trying to use common sense and explain to them, they are mistaken. Shireroth perhaps void of common sense has persisted with it's half ass claim. Amerada doesn't recognize any secession occurred as should anyone with common sense and more power to them. <br>
<br>
I believe I will start counting the days until Shireroth snaps out of it's self imposed delusion over this incident. I believe by the landsraad post it's been at least 16 days. We'll see how long this persists. <br>
