In the Republic of Amerada, Califario is a colony. Colonies are administrative, autonomous divisions of the Republic of Amerada. Territories are independent states which have cultural ties to Amerada. In a territory you are not required to be a citizen of the Republic of Amerada. However, to be a citizen of any of Amerada's colonies, you have to be a citizen of the Republic of Amerada. That is not a theory. It's a fact. <br>
Earl Washburn (who now calls himself &quot;Andrew Dussault&quot; , former President of Amerada, along with his accomplice Chris Sullivan (also known as &quot;TXsocialist&quot; attempted to overthrow the legitimately elected government of the Republic of Amerada. Some time earlier, Matt resigned his positions in Amerada (that included Governier of Califario) and renounced citizenship. He could not therefore, have been a citizen of Califario, since he was not a citizen of Amerada. He even offered to give the codes for the Califario ezboard to the new Governier, when appointed. <br>
Nevertheless, when Earl and his associate proclaimed his communist revolution, Matt claimed to withdraw Califario from Amerada. When the time was appropriate, and a new ezboard prepared, I crushed Earl's rebellion. Defeated, he changed his ezboard in a &quot;World Government Simulation&quot; and the revolution was over. <br>
Recently I appointed Angus McSoto Governier of Califario. I asked Matt to send him the codes for the board. Matt replied that he had given Califario to Shireroth. When informed that they had been misinformed, Shireroth persisted in its mistaken claim. I have since made a final statement on that subject at their board. I do not wish to further enflame the issue, but since you asked, I have given my opinion on the issue. <br>
